label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg01

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective. It has neurites in the posterior lateral protocerebrum, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, epaulette, vest, gnathal ganglion, neck neuropil, wing neuropil and intermediate tectulum. It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord. There is a cluster of up to ten of these cells in each hemisphere.

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg02

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective, but also has contralateral innervation (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the inferior clamp, inferior bridge, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, gnathal ganglion, wing neuropil and intermediate tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024). There is a cluster of up to fifteen of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg03

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord. There is a cluster of up to five of these cells in each hemisphere.

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg04

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg05

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the lateral subesophageal zone (Namiki et al., 2018; Sterne et al., 2021). This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018; Sterne et al., 2021). In the brain, it has dendritic arborization in the gnathal ganglion, saddle and inferior posterior slope (Sterne et al., 2021). In the ventral nerve cord, it fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle (Namiki et al., 2018) and has axonal arborization in the neck neuropil and wing neuropil (Sterne et al., 2021). There are up to four of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg06

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective. It has neurites in the wedge, inferior posterior slope, gnathal ganglion and wing neuropil. It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord. There is a cluster of up to four of these cells in each hemisphere.

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg07

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). In the brain it innervates zones A and B of the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (Vaughan et al., 2014), as well as the saddle, inferior posterior slope and gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It has bilateral arbors in the brain, descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective, then fasciculates with the contralateral intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle and innervates the intermediate tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). There is a cluster of up to seven of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018; Sturner et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018) identify this as being morphologically similar to VGlut-F-500136, described by FlyCircuit (FBrf0212704). Might be equivalent to or overlap with aSG-a (Vaughan et al., 2014).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg09

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). This neuron crosses the midline and descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the saddle, antennal mechanosensory and motor center, inferior posterior slope, gnathal ganglion, neck neuropil and intermediate tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024). There is a cluster of up to four of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg10

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. It fasciculates with the intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord. There is a cluster of up to fifteen of these cells in each hemisphere.

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg11

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It has dendrites in the superior posterior slope and gnathal ganglion, mainly in the ipsilateral hemisphere, and a large axon descending on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective to the intermediate tectulum, spanning all three thoracic neuromeres (Namiki et al., 2018; Guo et al., 2022). An axon crosses the midline in the brain and is indirectly connected to contralateral DNg11 neurons (Guo et al., 2022). It fasciculates with the intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There are usually three of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018; Guo et al., 2022). Its activity is associated with bilateral front leg grooming (Guo et al., 2022).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg12

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). Its dendrites arborize extensively in the gnathal ganglion, where it receives input from mechanosensory bristle neurons of the head, and its axon projects via the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective to the ipsilateral T1 leg neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018; Guo et al., 2022). There is a cluster of up to ten of these cells in each hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). Its activity induces ipsilateral ventral head and front leg grooming (Guo et al., 2022).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the antennal grooming descending neuron 1 (FBbt:00111647), described by Hampel et al. (2015) (FBrf0229838), but Guo et al. (2022) consider these to be distinct. Synaptic input from mechanosensory neurons of chaeta determined by GRASP (Guo et al., 2022).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg13

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective, but also has contralateral innervation (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the lateral accessory lobe, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, epaulette, vest, gnathal ganglion, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the ventral lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg14

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the dorsal lateral tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg15

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the anterior ventral gnathal ganglion (Matsuo et al., 2016; Namiki et al., 2018). The primary neurite extends posteriodorsomedially to form postsynaptic terminals bilaterally in the gnathal ganglion, as well as the contralateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center zones B and E, and saddle (Matsuo et al., 2016). It descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective and fasciculates with the ventral lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle (Namiki et al., 2018). In the VNC, it innervates the intermediate tectulum and T1 and T2 leg neuropils (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018).

definition.value: The location of presynaptic terminals could not be determined (Matsuo et al., 2016).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg24

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the lateroanterior gnathal ganglion (Matsuo et al., 2016; Namiki et al., 2018). The primary neurite extends posterioventromedially along the ventral edge of the anterior gnathal ganglion, then turns dorsally, arborizing in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A, B and E, saddle, gnathal ganglion and wedge (Matsuo et al., 2016). A thin fiber crosses the midline ventral to the esophagus, then turns ventrally to arborize in the contralateral saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion, before leaving the brain (Matsuo et al., 2016). A branch of the contralateral projection also arborizes in the AMMC zones A and B (Matsuo et al., 2016). Postsynaptic terminals are found in the AMMC in both hemispheres and presynaptic terminals are found in the contralateral saddle and the bilateral gnathal ganglion (Matsuo et al., 2016). It descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective, fasciculates with the ventral medial tract of the ventral cervical fascicle and innervates the intermediate tectulum, and T1 and T2 median ventral association centers (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg25

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion. This neuron crosses the midline and descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective. It has neurites in the flange, superior medial protocerebrum, gnathal ganglion, wing neuropil, haltere neuropil and abdominal neuromere. Its axonal projections follow a ventral route through the ventral nerve cord. There is one of these cells per hemisphere.

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to one of the CCAP-expressing neurons (FBbt:00111316), described by Lee et al. (2013) (FBrf0222983).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg27

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective, but also has contralateral innervation (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the inferior clamp, inferior bridge, cantle, flange, prow, superior posterior slope, gnathal ganglion and wing neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the median dorsal abdominal tract in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic and glutamatergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg28

value.value: Serotonergic descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a large cell body in the SE1 cluster, in the lateral part of the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Alekseyenko et al., 2010; Namiki et al., 2018; Yao and Scott, 2022). It has dendrites in the flange, prow and gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018; Yao and Scott, 2022) and it responds to bitter taste stimuli from the proboscis and legs (Yao and Scott, 2022). This neuron does not cross the midline and it sends an axonal projection via the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective to the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018; Yao and Scott, 2022). It also sends projections into the labial nerve and to the hypocerebral ganglion, via the recurrent nerve (Yao and Scott, 2022). It activates enteric neurons that express serotonin receptors and can stimulate crop contraction (Yao and Scott, 2022). There are two of these cells per hemisphere (Alekseyenko et al., 2010; Namiki et al., 2018; Yao and Scott, 2022).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg29

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a cell body in the cell body rind around the gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the saddle, antennal mechanosensory and motor center, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, wedge, gnathal ganglion and lower tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the dorsal lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center Db7 neuron (FBbt:00111502), described by Matsuo et al. (2016) (FBrf0230862).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg30

value.value: Adult serotonergic descending neuron belonging to the DNg group, having a large cell body in the cell body rind of the lateral gnathal ganglion (Namiki et al., 2018; Scheunemann et al., 2018). One branch projects dorsally to arborize and form presynapses in the ipsilateral anterior and posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, superior clamp and superior lateral protocerebrum (Scheunemann et al., 2018). Another branch crosses the midline just ventral to the esophageal foramen and arborizes in the contralateral gnathal ganglion and saddle, where it also forms presynapses (Scheunemann et al., 2018). It descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective, then fasciculates with the dorsal lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle and innervates the intermediate and lower tectulum, and the abdominal neuromere (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018; Scheunemann et al., 2018). Its superior clamp arbor outputs to MB-MP1 in the mushroom body pedunculus and it is involved in the initial period of long-term memory consolidation (Scheunemann et al., 2018). It also expresses the sex peptide receptor and myoinhibitory peptide (Mip/AstB) (Scheunemann et al., 2019).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the inferior contralateral interneuron, described by Jiang et al. (2013) (FBrf0222685).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg34

value.value: Adult fruitless-expressing octopaminergic descending neuron of the DNg group, having a cell body near the midline of the anterior gnathal ganglion (Yu et al., 2010; Certel et al., 2010; Namiki et al., 2018), in the mandibular segment (Busch and Tanimoto, 2010). It forms bilaterally symmetric arbors in the ventromedial neuropils and the subesophageal zone (Busch et al., 2009; Namiki et al., 2018). It descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective and fasciculates with the ventral lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle (Namiki et al., 2018). In the VNC, it innervates the T1, T2 and T3 leg neuropils and the abdominal neuromere, ipsilaterally (Busch et al., 2009; Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is glutamatergic as well as octopaminergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identified this as being morphologically similar to the octopaminergic VPM1 neuron (FBbt:00110149), described by Busch et al. (2009) (FBrf0207458) and the fruitless aDT8 neuron (FBbt:00110543), described by Yu et al. (2010) (FBrf0211884) - confirmed by Sturner et al. (2024) - doi:10.1101/2024.06.04.596633.

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp02

value.value: Fruitless-expressing descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a large cell body posterior to the posterior lateral protocerebrum (Kimura et al., 2008; Matsuo et al., 2016; Namiki et al., 2018). In the brain, its postsynapses are found in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center zones A and B, wedge and the LC4 glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (Matsuo et al., 2016). It has presynapses in the gnathal ganglion and saddle (Matsuo et al., 2016). It does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). In the VNC it follows the ventral medial tract of the ventral cervical fascicle and innervates the intermediate and lower tectulum, and the T2 leg neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018). It receives looming stimulus input from anterior LC4 neurons and its activity results in a backwards leaning posture and backwards takeoff (Dombrovski et al., 2023). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Matsuo et al., 2016; Namiki et al., 2018) and it is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the lateral giant descending neuron, described by Milde and Strausfeld (1990) (FBrf0239829).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp03

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body on the posterior surface of the brain. This neuron crosses the midline and descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective. It has neurites in the posterior lateral protocerebrum, wedge, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, gnathal ganglion, neck neuropil, wing neuropil, haltere neuropil and intermediate tectulum. It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord. There is one of these cells per hemisphere.

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to Cha-F-200252, described by FlyCircuit (FBrf0212704).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp04

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body on the posterior surface of the brain (Namiki et al., 2018). This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, gnathal ganglion and lower tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the ventral medial tract of the ventral cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024). It receives a large amount of its input from LC4 visual projection neurons (Dombrovski et al., 2023).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the ipsilateral small descending neuron, described by Milde and Strausfeld (1990) (FBrf0239829).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp05

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body posterior to the inferior clamp (Matsuo et al., 2016; Namiki et al., 2018). The primary neurite extends anteriorly and bifurcates in the gorget, with a lateral branch projecting ventrolaterally to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center zone B, wedge, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, including the LC4 glomerulus, posterior lateral protocerebrum, gorget and superior posterior slope (Matsuo et al., 2016). A medial branch crosses the midline, extends posterioventrally and forms presynaptic terminals in the contralateral saddle and both sides of the gnathal ganglion (Matsuo et al., 2016). It descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective, fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle and innervates the intermediate tectulum, T1, T2 and T3 leg neuropils (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the contralateral giant mimetic descending neuron, described by Milde and Strausfeld (1990) (FBrf0239829), VGlut-F-500311, described by FlyCircuit (FBrf0212704).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp06

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body posterior to the posterior to the posterior lateral protocerebrum (Matsuo et al., 2016; Namiki et al., 2018). The primary neurite extends anteriomedially, turns ventrally at the medial side of the PLP and branches, to form postsynaptic terminals in the ipsilateral antennal mechanosensory and motor center (AMMC) zones A and B, wedge, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (AVLP), the LC4 glomerulus of the posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum (PVLP), inferior clamp and gorget (Matsuo et al., 2016). A branch extends posterioventrally to form presynaptic terminals in the saddle and posterior gnathal ganglion (Matsuo et al., 2016). It does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective, then fasciculates with the dorsal lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to the inferior giant descending neuron, described by Milde and Strausfeld (1990) (FBrf0239829), the antennal mechanosensory and motor center Di5 neuron (FBbt:00111490), described by Matsuo et al. (2016) (FBrf0230862) and VGlut-F-900015, described by FlyCircuit (FBrf0212704).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp07

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body on the posterior surface of the brain. This neuron crosses the midline and descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective. It has neurites in the inferior clamp, superior clamp, superior lateral protocerebrum, posterior lateral protocerebrum, epaulette, vest, intermediate tectulum, lower tectulum, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil. It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord. There is one of these cells per hemisphere.

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp08

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body on the posterior surface of the brain (Namiki et al., 2018). This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the inferior bridge, saddle, superior posterior slope, epaulette, vest, gnathal ganglion and intermediate tectulum (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the ventral lateral tract of the ventral cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic and glutamatergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Namiki et al. (2018), identify this as being morphologically similar to VGlut-F-500767, described by FlyCircuit (FBrf0212704).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp09

value.value: Descending neuron belonging to the DNp group, having a cell body on the posterior surface of the brain (Namiki et al., 2018). This neuron does not cross the midline and descends on the ipsilateral side of the cervical connective (Namiki et al., 2018). It has neurites in the inferior clamp, anterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, wedge, posterior ventrolateral protocerebrum, inferior posterior slope, superior posterior slope, gorget, gnathal ganglion, intermediate tectulum, abdominal neuromere, T1 leg neuropil, T2 leg neuropil and T3 leg neuropil (Namiki et al., 2018). It fasciculates with the intermediate tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). Its higher cerebral arborization is dendritic and its subesophageal and ventral nerve cord arborization is axonal (Bidaye et al., 2020). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018). It is cholinergic (Cheong et al., 2024). It receives strong input from lobula columnar LC9 neurons (Bidaye et al., 2020). It can initiate forwards walking, with an ipsilateral turning component and it involved in orientation behavior (Bidaye et al., 2020).

definition.value: Freezing behavior observed by Zacarias et al. (2018) - FBrf0240068 only seen in one of four genotypes by Bidaye et al. (2020).

It fasciculates with the median tract of the dorsal cervical fascicle in the ventral nerve cord (Namiki et al., 2018). There is one of these cells per hemisphere (Namiki et al., 2018).
